Company asked for role preference
but shortlisted according to
business requirements
CTC given by the company is 7.64 while 10.64 is the money received post retention and joining bonus. So considered 10.64 as CTC with 7.64 as base

CTC: Total Earning Potential will be Base + Variable + Other benefits [Variable Pay - which depends on the individual’s performance, service line’s performance and the firm’s performance + Other Benefits (Gratuity & Insurance)]
There are other allowances that might be provided which is not part of the CTC. Only a few have been offered the itnernship
Hiring for internship only with PBC
10 inclusive of fixed + variable, Additional 1.5 JB
Internship with PBC. Internship duration - 6 months to 1 Yr

4 got PPO ( 1 of them rejected offer)
CTC = ~40LPA (Not exactly 40) -> RSUs worth Rs 16L + 8L Insurance and other Benefits

13L Base + 1.5L JB + 1.25L Relocation 
+ 4L  Annual Incentive Compensation (Performace Based)
This is from the Code for Good for FTE
Took students through CTY program held on collaboration with CCBD (RR Campus Exclusive)
3 of the 4 were given the offer and all 3 accepted it
Benefits included such as free cab and stuff. Additional 1.25L for Relocation Bonus
Coding Test was Medium Hard Level, Shortlisted 25 for 1st Round, Open to All depts
Technical Test was held 2 times. The first technical test was very easy. Second Techincal Test was held in Campus

Shortlisted 102 students (based on Resume), Support - Tested more on Project Understanding, Current Technologies, Theory Fundamentals (OS,CN, DBMS), Less of DSA. Dev tested more of DSA/Problem solving, QE was a mix

3 Qs (LL, Greedy, Backtracking) + 20 MCQs (CN, OOPS, Cpp, Linux), Conducted 4 Rounds of interview (3DSA/Project - 1HR), Selected 6 out 7 PPL who reached HR round, Shortlisted around 30 PPL for first round interview

OA Tips: Majorly focus on coding quickly (70 min, 4 problems) and learn String manipulation in ur language (substr in cpp) only after which logic can be used , 2 Rounds, 1st was DSA (Tree DFS problem), 2nd Round was OOPS (system design) (Design building with floors, gym,cafe) Last was HR.
Questions Lifted Directly from Codeforces Problems. Shortlisted 18 ppl for interview
Sectional Timer Test - I Applied for QA - All MCQ (Aptitude 15Q-20Min), Tech(45 Mcq - 60Min). For SDE they had Coding as well 2DSAI
Sectional Timer Test - 3 Sections - Aptitude (15Q-20Min), Technical (10Q), DSA(2Coding-40Min) - String & Min Spanning Tree
Sectional Timer Test - 3 Sections - Aptitude (15Q-20Min), Technical (10Q), DSA(2Coding-40Min)
Open for All, 2 coding in 1 hr, shortlisted 200+ PPL for Interview divided into Different roles/Domains (Automation, D&Ai)
Open to all depts, Relocation to HYD on our own, Shortlisted 38 for next round. Includes Project Round where you had to complete a task given by the team in few days deadline

Shortlisted 90 People for Interviews (2 Round), Dream company (>60 lpa), Open for all (even ones holding offer), Had 2 tests, 1st one had 2 Coding (Greedy - https://leetcode.com/problems/jump-game/ , 1 Graph, 10 MCQs (DBMS, Oops, DSA) due to technical glitch had to retest, 2nd and Final test - Had 2 Coding (1-Similar to https://leetcode.com/problems/reverse-pairs/ , other one was Sliding window + Binary Search) and 5 MCQs (DSA, Os(kernal/system threads) in 1 hr 10 mins
Asked DP, Graph, 1 SQL problem, 10 aptitude... Sectional wise
Shortlisted 108 for Interview, 2 Tests (1st - 4 coding, 23 MCQs, 1.5 hrs... 2nd - 3 coding(Valid BST Iterative, Addition of Binary strings, Youngest Member not in array), 15 MCQs 1.5 hrs)
Shortlisted 9+ CGPA for OA (~100 people), Shortlisted 30 for Interview
Shortlisted 45 people across dept for interview, Had 1 round interview 1 case study round, Questions asked on Guess estimate problems (Opening a Dress Shop in Bangalore, Profit margin in Tires)
Shortlisted 30+ ppl for Interview, 2 Rounds (2nd one being OOPS system design based round)
